<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I am building a simple tool which can access the contactlist from a MSN Live account but something is bugging me. I am using a Zend_Http_Client object to do all the calls and I am using the Zend_Http_Cookiejar to store cookies in. During the calls the cookies get properly saved with host ".live.com" so they are accessible from all subdomains. I tried getting the cookie by:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$cookiejar = $client-&gt;getCookieJar();
$authcookie = $cookiejar-&gt;getCookie('<a href="">http://.live.com</a>', 'MSPAuth');
</code></pre>

<p>This gives me an Exception with "Invalid URI supplied" as message. When i remove the dot from the URI I don't get an exception but the CookieJar won't return the cookie since the host doesnt match (live.com != .live.com). When I remove the check for the hostname in Zend_Uri the ".live.com" hostname is working fine like this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$uri = Zend_Uri::factory();
$uri-&gt;setHost('.live.com');
$authcookie = $cookiejar-&gt;getCookie($uri, 'MSPAuth');
</code></pre>

<p>Please fix, tnx :)</p>

